text: I remember buying this game Day 1, so excited to play the sequel to one of my favorites games of all time. The intro with the storybook and this theme actually gave me a good first impression, but it didn't take long for me to understand this was not to be the sequel I had wished for. Still, this theme will probably be stuck in my head forever.
author: SupraDarky

text: I had the same issue. I was hoping for more Yoshi's Island and didn't get that, but I still have lots of fond memories of this game. To be honest, that's kind of my feelings for everything on the N64 compared to the SNES.
author: Jared Silvestri

text: Not having played Yoshi's Island beforehand, I thought Yoshi's Story was decent at release even though it felt short and easy. But as with all games back then I tried to squeeze out all the game had to offer so I set myself the goal to get all 30 melons (not water melons) in each level (all hearts as well) which made the game much more fun, explorative and challenging.
